[
    {
        "text": "- This is a mud volcano.",
        "start": 0.15,
        "duration": 2.346
    },
    {
        "text": "(mud bubbling)",
        "start": 2.496,
        "duration": 1.394
    },
    {
        "text": "And I spent four hours",
        "start": 3.89,
        "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
        "text": "dragging my production\nteam around the desert,",
        "start": 5.79,
        "duration": 1.72
    },
    {
        "text": "looking for mud volcanoes",
        "start": 7.51,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "that were right off the side of the road.",
        "start": 8.83,
        "duration": 1.88
    },
    {
        "text": "For a little context,",
        "start": 10.71,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "we had driven out to the Salton Sea,",
        "start": 11.543,
        "duration": 2.287
    },
    {
        "text": "which if you haven't heard of it,",
        "start": 13.83,
        "duration": 0.98
    },
    {
        "text": "is this really weird man-made\npseudo accident of a lake,",
        "start": 14.81,
        "duration": 4.15
    },
    {
        "text": "that used to be a huge attraction",
        "start": 18.96,
        "duration": 1.35
    },
    {
        "text": "for the Hollywood star types.",
        "start": 20.31,
        "duration": 1.19
    },
    {
        "text": "- I've never been there,",
        "start": 21.5,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "and so I see this like huge sea.",
        "start": 22.333,
        "duration": 2.317
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm like, wow, that is pretty impressive.",
        "start": 24.65,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "And then, you know,",
        "start": 26.57,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "you put your window\ndown, and you smell it.",
        "start": 27.403,
        "duration": 1.317
    },
    {
        "text": "You're like, I don't\nactually need to go up to it,",
        "start": 28.72,
        "duration": 1.85
    },
    {
        "text": "or do anything near it.",
        "start": 30.57,
        "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
        "text": "- That's Carolina Zamora,",
        "start": 32.47,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "the geologists who you might\nremember from my last video,",
        "start": 33.72,
        "duration": 2.42
    },
    {
        "text": "on the strange mud puddle\nmoving across the desert.",
        "start": 36.14,
        "duration": 2.95
    },
    {
        "text": "We were in the area to film that video,",
        "start": 39.09,
        "duration": 1.64
    },
    {
        "text": "cause, how could you not?",
        "start": 40.73,
        "duration": 1.39
    },
    {
        "text": "What a bizarre thing.",
        "start": 42.12,
        "duration": 1.26
    },
    {
        "text": "But I soon found out about\nthese really cool mud volcanoes,",
        "start": 43.38,
        "duration": 2.9
    },
    {
        "text": "which are holes in the ground,",
        "start": 46.28,
        "duration": 0.87
    },
    {
        "text": "that let up CO2,",
        "start": 47.15,
        "duration": 1.28
    },
    {
        "text": "that then drags water\nthrough dusty sediment,",
        "start": 48.43,
        "duration": 2.41
    },
    {
        "text": "and forms these bubbling,\nmuddy holes in the ground.",
        "start": 50.84,
        "duration": 3.51
    },
    {
        "text": "And then if they don't move,",
        "start": 54.35,
        "duration": 0.99
    },
    {
        "text": "they slowly build up mounds,",
        "start": 55.34,
        "duration": 1.28
    },
    {
        "text": "like a volcano,",
        "start": 56.62,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "which sounded awesome.",
        "start": 57.92,
        "duration": 1.69
    },
    {
        "text": "Unless you're Hannah,",
        "start": 59.61,
        "duration": 0.85
    },
    {
        "text": "she gave them one star.",
        "start": 60.46,
        "duration": 1.04
    },
    {
        "text": "The thing that really\ndid deserve one star,",
        "start": 61.5,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "was my role,",
        "start": 63.21,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "as expedition leader.",
        "start": 64.51,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": "Here's how it went down,",
        "start": 65.8,
        "duration": 1.05
    },
    {
        "text": "as a person living in the year 2021,",
        "start": 66.85,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "I pulled up a map on my phone of the route",
        "start": 69.13,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "to get to the mud volcanoes,",
        "start": 71.35,
        "duration": 1.63
    },
    {
        "text": "but the main road to them, was gated off.",
        "start": 72.98,
        "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
        "text": "We talked to the person\nwho managed that area,",
        "start": 75.48,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "who told us that the\noriginal closed gated road,",
        "start": 77.76,
        "duration": 2.82
    },
    {
        "text": "was correct.",
        "start": 80.58,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "So we drove back,",
        "start": 81.413,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "parked outside and decided to try to hike",
        "start": 82.246,
        "duration": 1.944
    },
    {
        "text": "the two miles down the road.",
        "start": 84.19,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "And we soon realized why it was closed.",
        "start": 85.72,
        "duration": 2.47
    },
    {
        "text": "See, there's something\nunique about this area",
        "start": 88.19,
        "duration": 2.11
    },
    {
        "text": "that can create mudpots.",
        "start": 90.3,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "Check this out.",
        "start": 91.98,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "There's a really cool site\ncalled topographicmap.com,",
        "start": 92.813,
        "duration": 2.237
    },
    {
        "text": "where you can click around\nand see the elevation.",
        "start": 95.05,
        "duration": 1.82
    },
    {
        "text": "For example,",
        "start": 96.87,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "there's an impressive\n2000 feet of difference",
        "start": 97.703,
        "duration": 1.677
    },
    {
        "text": "from just here to here.",
        "start": 99.38,
        "duration": 1.21
    },
    {
        "text": "And then you click here,\nand it goes negative.",
        "start": 100.59,
        "duration": 2.42
    },
    {
        "text": "And that's not an error.",
        "start": 103.01,
        "duration": 1.08
    },
    {
        "text": "That's a basin,",
        "start": 104.09,
        "duration": 1.06
    },
    {
        "text": "the Salton Trough,",
        "start": 105.15,
        "duration": 1.113
    },
    {
        "text": "which is over 200 feet below sea level.",
        "start": 107.32,
        "duration": 2.67
    },
    {
        "text": "How does something in the\nmiddle of a continent,",
        "start": 109.99,
        "duration": 1.93
    },
    {
        "text": "get below sea level?",
        "start": 111.92,
        "duration": 1.33
    },
    {
        "text": "So over the last 5 million years,",
        "start": 113.25,
        "duration": 2.09
    },
    {
        "text": "the Pacific and North American plates,",
        "start": 115.34,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": "tectonic plates,",
        "start": 117.11,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "have actually been\nsliding past one another.",
        "start": 117.943,
        "duration": 1.657
    },
    {
        "text": "So that, Los Angeles is\nmoving toward San Francisco.",
        "start": 119.6,
        "duration": 2.66
    },
    {
        "text": "And this is still happening,",
        "start": 122.26,
        "duration": 1.61
    },
    {
        "text": "at about the same rate as your nails grow.",
        "start": 123.87,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "But it's not constant.",
        "start": 126.59,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "It's as if your nails didn't grow",
        "start": 127.89,
        "duration": 1.94
    },
    {
        "text": "for a hundred years,",
        "start": 129.83,
        "duration": 1.05
    },
    {
        "text": "and then, boom!",
        "start": 130.88,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "They grow 20 feet in a day,",
        "start": 131.713,
        "duration": 1.577
    },
    {
        "text": "and that's disruptive.",
        "start": 133.29,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "That's when big earthquakes happen.",
        "start": 134.75,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Like this one in San Francisco in 1906,",
        "start": 136.75,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "that ignited a three day fire,",
        "start": 139.31,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "that destroyed 500 city blocks.",
        "start": 141.11,
        "duration": 2.71
    },
    {
        "text": "The San Andreas fault,",
        "start": 143.82,
        "duration": 0.92
    },
    {
        "text": "it doesn't just shake the ground.",
        "start": 144.74,
        "duration": 1.54
    },
    {
        "text": "It does something else,",
        "start": 146.28,
        "duration": 1.08
    },
    {
        "text": "a little unusual.",
        "start": 147.36,
        "duration": 1.15
    },
    {
        "text": "- So when you have this strikes up motion,",
        "start": 148.51,
        "duration": 1.99
    },
    {
        "text": "you'll start to move,",
        "start": 150.5,
        "duration": 1.19
    },
    {
        "text": "the faults will move,",
        "start": 151.69,
        "duration": 0.89
    },
    {
        "text": "and then, you'll actually\nget some extension.",
        "start": 152.58,
        "duration": 2.31
    },
    {
        "text": "You'll get some, some opening.",
        "start": 154.89,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "- This extension process creates a Graben,",
        "start": 157.23,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "which is a word that means\na sunken area of land,",
        "start": 160.35,
        "duration": 2.47
    },
    {
        "text": "that comes from the German word for grave.",
        "start": 162.82,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "The sinking process is\nso violent and vast,",
        "start": 164.98,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "that this area should actually be",
        "start": 167.7,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "thousands of feet deep into the earth.",
        "start": 169.4,
        "duration": 1.93
    },
    {
        "text": "But then the Colorado River came in,",
        "start": 171.33,
        "duration": 1.93
    },
    {
        "text": "and brought sediment.",
        "start": 173.26,
        "duration": 1.06
    },
    {
        "text": "And then the plates pulled apart,",
        "start": 174.32,
        "duration": 1.16
    },
    {
        "text": "and the river came and brought sediment,",
        "start": 175.48,
        "duration": 1.16
    },
    {
        "text": "plates pulled apart\nand so on and so forth,",
        "start": 176.64,
        "duration": 1.41
    },
    {
        "text": "for so many millennia,",
        "start": 178.05,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "that some areas have actually been filled",
        "start": 179.57,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": "with up to 20,000 feet of sediment.",
        "start": 181.05,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "20,000 feet!",
        "start": 183.18,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "And that's just all under your feet,",
        "start": 184.7,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "as you're walking around there.",
        "start": 186.56,
        "duration": 1.19
    },
    {
        "text": "It's honestly kind of\nsurprising that the area is",
        "start": 187.75,
        "duration": 1.66
    },
    {
        "text": "only 200 feet below sea level.",
        "start": 189.41,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": "The thing about an area below sea level,",
        "start": 191.87,
        "duration": 1.99
    },
    {
        "text": "is that it can flood.",
        "start": 193.86,
        "duration": 1.43
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, any flat dry area can flood.",
        "start": 195.29,
        "duration": 2.481
    },
    {
        "text": "(bird squawking)",
        "start": 197.771,
        "duration": 2.239
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah, he agrees.",
        "start": 200.01,
        "duration": 0.93
    },
    {
        "text": "So we're walking down the\nroad on our mudpot mission,",
        "start": 200.94,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "to find that the road had flooded.",
        "start": 202.92,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": "We'd step on the ground and this black,",
        "start": 204.87,
        "duration": 1.35
    },
    {
        "text": "tar water would come up\nand cover your shoes.",
        "start": 206.22,
        "duration": 2.2
    },
    {
        "text": "And my next mistake,",
        "start": 208.42,
        "duration": 0.99
    },
    {
        "text": "was that I was following\nsatellite imagery on the phone,",
        "start": 209.41,
        "duration": 2.12
    },
    {
        "text": "but we get to a place,",
        "start": 211.53,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "where we just, cannot go any farther.",
        "start": 212.363,
        "duration": 1.797
    },
    {
        "text": "Because what the satellite didn't show,",
        "start": 214.16,
        "duration": 1.78
    },
    {
        "text": "is that the entire area had flooded,",
        "start": 215.94,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "and turned into a massive wetland.",
        "start": 218.07,
        "duration": 1.81
    },
    {
        "text": "And it's all marshes,",
        "start": 219.88,
        "duration": 1.14
    },
    {
        "text": "and there's almost over head high stocks",
        "start": 221.02,
        "duration": 1.83
    },
    {
        "text": "of grassy stuff that were un-passable.",
        "start": 222.85,
        "duration": 2.23
    },
    {
        "text": "So it's three hours later,",
        "start": 225.08,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "and I had just about given up,",
        "start": 226.6,
        "duration": 1.16
    },
    {
        "text": "and we resigned to go check out these",
        "start": 227.76,
        "duration": 1.62
    },
    {
        "text": "little mud mountains,",
        "start": 229.38,
        "duration": 0.87
    },
    {
        "text": "right off the main road,",
        "start": 230.25,
        "duration": 0.87
    },
    {
        "text": "that I thought were\ndormant, mud volcanoes.",
        "start": 231.12,
        "duration": 2.86
    },
    {
        "text": "It was the end of the day, we'd given up.",
        "start": 233.98,
        "duration": 1.4
    },
    {
        "text": "So we parked the car and walk over.",
        "start": 235.38,
        "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
        "text": "And as we get closer,",
        "start": 237.28,
        "duration": 1.22
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm hearing what I\nthink is faint bubbling.",
        "start": 238.5,
        "duration": 2.44
    },
    {
        "text": "No way!",
        "start": 240.94,
        "duration": 1.35
    },
    {
        "text": "We get up to them, and they are going off.",
        "start": 242.29,
        "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
        "text": "There's what looked like a\nfresh eruption from that day.",
        "start": 245.05,
        "duration": 2.92
    },
    {
        "text": "There were these bubbling bursting,",
        "start": 247.97,
        "duration": 2.11
    },
    {
        "text": "small burblers and big, giant bubbles.",
        "start": 250.08,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "And it was so cool.",
        "start": 252.33,
        "duration": 2.131
    },
    {
        "text": "(mud bubbling)",
        "start": 254.461,
        "duration": 2.583
    },
    {
        "text": "So after all that hiking,",
        "start": 263.13,
        "duration": 1.55
    },
    {
        "text": "the bushes,",
        "start": 264.68,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "they were right there.",
        "start": 265.513,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "Literally visible from the road,",
        "start": 266.346,
        "duration": 2.224
    },
    {
        "text": "whatever.",
        "start": 268.57,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "Mudpots are so random,",
        "start": 269.403,
        "duration": 2.357
    },
    {
        "text": "they're so cool.",
        "start": 271.76,
        "duration": 0.93
    },
    {
        "text": "And because of the San Andreas fault line,",
        "start": 272.69,
        "duration": 2.21
    },
    {
        "text": "and the 5 million years\nof sediment forming here,",
        "start": 274.9,
        "duration": 2.3
    },
    {
        "text": "it's the perfect location\nfor the sediment to make",
        "start": 277.2,
        "duration": 2.71
    },
    {
        "text": "beautifully erupting mud pots.",
        "start": 279.91,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "But, they don't usually move.",
        "start": 282.19,
        "duration": 2.203
    }
]